# Code Quality

- Keep functions focused and usually under ~50 lines.
- Prefer early returns over deep nesting; avoid nesting deeper than 4 levels.
- Keep cyclomatic complexity low; extract helpers when branches represent separate concepts.
- Handle errors at the right boundary: convert low-level errors to domain/structured errors before exposing them.
- Add tests around changed behavior when risk or blast radius is meaningful.
- Avoid broad refactors while fixing a narrow issue unless the refactor directly reduces risk.
